parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold gasket can cause coolant to leak into the engine, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potential engine failure.
symptoms: Coolant leaks
overheating
temperature gauge fluctuations
loss of heat
sweet or antifreeze smell in the engine compartment
engine stalling or hesitation
and check engine light illumination.

power window malfunctions
electrical system failures
and engine stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk, hesitate, or refuse to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission shifts hard
hesitates
or refuses to shift
the vehicle jerks or hesitates when accelerating
the transmission makes a loud clanking or grinding noise
the vehicle's engine dies

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The slipping and hard shifting of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or jerk, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting
the transmission shifts hard or abruptly
the vehicle jerks or hesitates when accelerating
the transmission makes a loud clanking or grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission bearing can cause the transmission to fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission makes a loud clanking or grinding noise
the transmission warning light comes on
the vehicle's engine dies
the transmission shifts hard or hesitates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle while using cruise control can lead to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates uncontrollably
often to high speeds
when the cruise control is engaged or turned on
but not necessarily activated. The acceleration can occur randomly
when resuming cruise control
or when using the turn signal. In some cases
the vehicle may continue to accelerate even when the brake pedal is tapped.
